,Recommended,330620,13365708,"Posted: 14 December, 2014",all,redp,"It's A Wipe is worth the money for the nostalgia factor, but most of the game feels relatively spartan in features or gameplay. Generally, the game consists of managing a sitcom-version of a guild raiding party in an indirect fashion with breaks in between; additional characters or other amusing features that one think to find in a game about managing a guild are absent.Further, the game is quickly over -- there seems to be only 7-8 raids -- and some of the mechanics really need some work, particularly infighting over loot. This can make the game frustrating and the game itself seems to have relatively little replayability; which is odd given that the overall concept of the game, if developed, could provide for a fascinating guild management game.The problem with that is that the game not developed sufficiently; it is, as stated, feature light.With that said, it's five dollars and I had trouble not liking it. For that price you get what you might expect. I would tepidly recommend the game and hope the developer fleshes out the features of it.Pros:-Interesting concept.-Nostalgia.-Humor is good.-Good framework for a game; seems easily developed.Cons:-Relatively thin in gameplay depth; feature light.-Sometimes frustrating.-Sometimes boring in some fights; cannot manage one's own character.-The UI is really very ugly."
