,Recommended,330620,22685355,"Posted: 28 April, 2016",all,Kiana,"Look at my time played. I have enjoyed every hour I've spent on this game.The developer is great about listening to the community, fixing bugs as they're found in a timely manner.I STRONGLY RECOMMEND not reading a guide before playing, since a major part of the gameplay is figuring out each boss' mechanics on your own.Essentially, IAW is a puzzle with multiple solutions. Which raiders you recruit, your group's class spread, balancing loot distribution, everything plays a part in your success, and there isn't a single 'right' answer. Do you take two rogues for higher damage, but knowing morale might suffer from loot disputes? Do you take two wizards, knowing they'll deal high damage, but have trouble swapping targets? Do you take a bard for the buffs or replace them with a different class?I've played through the game with a lot of different spreads. Once with three warriors, once with only one, sometimes I take a bard, sometimes I don't. Once I took two druids, even. It's all about figuring out how the group will interact and doing what you can to keep things balanced.Plus the humor is great. It's amusing even if you don't get the references, but is pretty great if you do.So microwave a burrito, turn on voice chat and grab the rum: It's time to go raiding."
