76561197996694721,Recommended,330620,34484216,Posted: 25 August,all,Catatöskr,"This is a simple game, that I enjoy a lot.The first few dungeons are easy enough, you'll find some loot and learn the basic game mechanics.At first you just have to tell raid members what to do. Healers heal, tanks tank, dps do damage.Then you get a bit of micromanagement to do.Sometimes raidmembers switch roles and you need to yell at them.Somtimes raidmembers stand in fire and you need at them.Sometimes the melee walk into the backline and you need to yell at them.Sometimes the tank gets low and you need to yell at the healers to keep them up (which works, unlike in World of Warcraft).Maybe a fight is too rough, so you go back to an older dungeon to gear up.Later the fights get complexer. You'll need to pay attention to mechanics and macro manage your raid as well as micro manage your raid at the same time.I find it enjoyable and considering it's price tag I'd recomend waiting for a sale."
